HEADWORD: Sea apple
<hw>Sea" ap"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The fruit of a
West Indian palm (<spn>Manicaria Plukenetii</spn>), often found floating
in the sea.</def> <rj><au>A. Grisebach.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

